  "Yes, because Brand B has more neutral responses": "",
  "Brand A: 180/300 = 60% satisfied. Brand B: 120/300 = 40% satisfied. The conditional distributions differ substantially (60% vs 40% satisfied), indicating an association between brand and satisfaction.": "",
